, Cheuk, Chi Wai, Chuen, Hon, Keung, Wah, Wai, Chiu, Ho.","Chinese: alternative Mandarin form of the surname 敖, see   Ao  .","Chinese: Cantonese form of the surnames 歐 and 區, see   Ou   1 and 2."],"variants":[{"name":"Auerbach","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Hyman, Moshe, Emanuel, Isidor, Bronia, Chaim, Faigy, Menachem, Meyer, Yechezkel.","German: habitational name from any of several places in southern Germany and Austria called Auerbach ‘the stream at the water meadow’. See also 2,   Au  , and   Bach  .","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name from the town of Auerbach in the Upper Palatinate, Bavaria. Compare   Averbach  ."]},{"name":"Ao","meanings":["Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 敖, meaning both ‘rambling’ and ‘deposed king without posthumous titles’ in ancient Chinese: (i) from the personal name of <i>Tai Ao</i> (太敖), teacher of the legendary king Zhuanxu (traditional dates: 2514–2437  BC ). (ii) it is said that the surname is also borne by descendants of deposed kings of the former state of Chu, with no posthumous titles, during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC )."]},{"name":"Auer","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Alois, Hans, Erwin, Matthias, Siegfried, Bernd, Bernhard, Erna, Franz, Fritz, Hermann, Horst.","German (mainly Bavaria): topographic name for someone living by a water meadow, German <i>Au</i>, or a habitational name for someone from a place called Au or Aue (see   Au   and   Aue  ). This surname is also found in France (Alsace and Lorraine), Czechia, and Slovenia."]}]},{"name":"Leuan","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Leaman  .","Flemish: status name for a feudal tenant or vassal, Dutch <i>leenman</i>. This surname is found in Belgium and France (mainly Nord). Compare Dutch   Leeman   1.","Polish: from German   Lehmann  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Leaman","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name or nickname <i>Lefman</i> (see   Lemon  ).","Americanized form of German   Lehmann  .","History: This (see 2 above) is one of the variants of the name of a Swiss Mennonite family, in the US most commonly spelled   Lehman  ."]}]},{"name":"Meuric","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Mauricius</i> via Old Welsh <i>Mouric</i>.  See  <b>Maurice</b>   ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Meuric ap Leuan was born in 1201, in Glamorgan, Wales, his father, Leuan Ap Seisyll, was 25 and his mother, Ann Verch Meuric, was 23. He had at least 2 sons with Lady Eva Verch Ythel. He died in 1264, in his hometown, at the age of 63."},"et":{"1201–1264":"1201–1264","1204–1254":"1204–1254","1226–1266":"1226–1266","1227–Male":"1227–Surnud","1176–1205":"1176–1205","1178–1205":"1178–1205","1205":"1205","1227":"1227","1226":"1226","1204":"1204","abt 1227":"umbes 1227","1201":"1201","1178":"1178","1266":"1266","1254":"1254","1264":"1264","1176":"1176","of Ystrad, Glams, Wals":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1201–1264":"1201–1264","1204–1254":"1204–1254","1226–1266":"1226–1266","1227–Male":"1227–Kuollut","1176–1205":"1176–1205","1178–1205":"1178–1205","1205":"1205","1227":"1227","1226":"1226","1204":"1204","abt 1227":"noin 1227","1201":"1201","1178":"1178","1266":"1266","1254":"1254","1264":"1264","1176":"1176","of Ystrad, Glams, Wals":"Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1201–1264":"1201–1264","1204–1254":"1204–1254","1226–1266":"1226–1266","1227–Male":"1227–Décédé","1176–1205":"1176–1205","1178–1205":"1178–1205","1205":"1205","1227":"1227","1226":"1226","1204":"1204","abt 1227":"environ 1227","1201":"1201","1178":"1178","1266":"1266","1254":"1254","1264":"1264","1176":"1176","of Ystrad, Glam